Code to solve conjugacy and centralizer problems for arbitrary elements
of classical groups. 

Below find list of top-level intrinsics.

To make these available: 

AttachSpec ("spec");

Giovanni de Franceschi and Eamonn O'Brien 
September 2020

=======================================================

>   InternalConjugacyClasses;
Intrinsic 'InternalConjugacyClasses'

Signatures:

    (type::MonStgElt, d::RngIntElt, q::RngIntElt) -> SeqEnum, SetIndx

        Conjugacy classes and their labels for the classical group of supplied type, rank 
        and field size.


* type is one of "GU",  "SU", "GO+", "GO-", "GO", "SO+", "SO-", "SO", "Omega+", "Omega-", "Omega"
e.g. C, L := InternalConjugacyClasses ("GO+", 8, 5);
     C, L := InternalConjugacyClasses ("Sp", 6, 4);


The class representatives are in the Magma copy of the classical group,
so in GOPlus (8, 5) and Sp (6, 4) respectively. 

InternalClasses is a synonym.

=======================================================

> ClassicalIsConjugate;                                                               
Intrinsic 'ClassicalIsConjugate'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, g::GrpMatElt, h::GrpMatElt) -> GrpMatElt

        If g and h are conjugate in classical group G, return true and 
        conjugating element, else false.

e.g. 
G := Sp (16, 5);
x := Random (G); y := Random (G);
f, z := ClassicalIsConjugate (G, x, x^y);
x^z eq x^y;

=======================================================

> ClassicalCentraliser;                                                               
Intrinsic 'ClassicalCentraliser'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, x::GrpMatElt) -> GrpMat

        Centraliser of element in classical group.

e.g. 

G := OmegaPlus (12, 5);
x := Random (G);
C := ClassicalCentraliser (G, x);

=======================================================

> ClassesForFixedSemisimple;
Intrinsic 'ClassesForFixedSemisimple'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMatElt, x::GrpMatElt) -> SeqEnum

        given a semisimple element x in the classical group G, return the list 
        of representatives of conjugacy classes in G with semisimple part x.
e.g. 

G := OmegaPlus (16, 9);
repeat x := Random (G); until IsSemisimple (x);
C := ClassesForFixedSemisimple (G, x);
C;

=======================================================

> SemisimpleClasses;
Intrinsic 'SemisimpleClasses'

Signatures:

    (type::MonStgElt, n::RngIntElt, F::FldFin) -> SeqEnum

        Semisimple conjugacy classes of the classical group of supplied type, 
        rank and field.

    (type::MonStgElt, n::RngIntElt, q::RngIntElt) -> SeqEnum

        Semisimple conjugacy classes of the classical group of supplied type, 
        rank and field size.

e.g. 
S := SemisimpleClasses ("SU", 7, 3);
#S;

=======================================================

> SemisimpleIsConjugate;
Intrinsic 'SemisimpleIsConjugate'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, g::GrpMatElt, h::GrpMatElt) -> GrpMatElt

        if semisimple g and h are conjugate in classical group G, return true 
        and conjugating element, else false.

e.g.
G := OmegaPlus (20, 5);
repeat x := Random (G); until IsSemisimple (x);
y := x^Random (G);
flag, c := SemisimpleIsConjugate (G, x, y);
assert x^c eq y;

=======================================================

> SemisimpleCentraliser;
Intrinsic 'SemisimpleCentraliser'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, g::GrpMatElt) -> GrpMat

        Centraliser of semisimple element in classical group G.

e.g. 
G := Sp (50, 5^2);
repeat x := Random (G); until IsSemisimple (x);
C := SemisimpleCentraliser (G, x);
#C;

