> UnipotentCentraliser;
Intrinsic 'UnipotentCentraliser'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, x::GrpMatElt) -> GrpMat

        Centralizer of unipotent eleement in classical group.

e.g.
G := GOPlus (8, 9);
repeat x := Random (G); until IsUnipotent (x);
C := UnipotentCentraliser (G, x);
#C;

=======================================================

> UnipotentIsConjugate;
Intrinsic 'UnipotentIsConjugate'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, x::GrpMatElt, y::GrpMatElt) -> GrpMatElt

        if unipotent g and h are conjugate in classical group G, return true and
        conjugating element, else false.

e.g.
G := GOPlus (14, 3);
repeat x := Random (G); until IsUnipotent (x);
y := x^Random (G);
flag, c := UnipotentIsConjugate (G, x, y);
flag;
x^c eq y;

=======================================================

> ClassicalClassSize;
Intrinsic 'ClassicalClassSize'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, g::GrpMatElt) -> RngIntElt, SeqEnum

        Size of conjugacy class and order of centraliser of g in classical group
        G.

e.g.
G := SU (10, 27);
x := Random (G);
a, b := ClassicalClassSize (G, x);
a; // Class size
b; // Factored order of centralizer 

==========================================

> UnipotentClassMap;
Intrinsic 'UnipotentClassMap'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, U::SeqEnum, L::SetIndx) -> Map
    [
        type
    ]

        U and L are output of UnipotentClasses, where U is sequence of unipotent
        class representative and L is the corresponding list of labels; return 
        unipotent class map for G.



e.g. 
U, L := UnipotentClasses ("Sp", 10, 9);
G := Sp (10, 9);
eta := UnipotentClassMap (G, U, L);
repeat g := Random (G); until IsUnipotent (g);
eta (g);

U, L := UnipotentClasses ("Omega+", 10, 8);
G := OmegaPlus (10, 8);
eta := UnipotentClassMap (G, U, L);
repeat g := Random (G); until IsUnipotent (g);
eta (g);

=======================================================

> InternalClassMap;
Intrinsic 'InternalClassMap'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, C::SeqEnum, L::SetIndx) -> Map
    [
        type
    ]

        C and L are output of InternalClasses, where C is sequence of classes and L is
        list of corresponding labels; return class map for G.



// this is now a map which can be applied to an element as in existing ClassMap
e.g. 
G := Sp (6, 5);
C, L := InternalClasses ("Sp", 6, 5);
eta := InternalClassMap (G, C, L);
x := Random (G);
eta (x);

=============================================================
> ClassLabel;
Intrinsic 'ClassLabel'

Signatures:

    (type::MonStgElt, x::GrpMatElt) -> SetMulti

        return class label for element x of corresponding isometry group G  
        determined by type; the labels of distinct elements of G agree if 
        and only if they are conjugate in G.

e.g.
G := GOPlus (8, 9);
x := Random (G); 
y := x^Random (G);
lx := ClassLabel ("GO+", x);
ly := ClassLabel ("GO+", y);
lx eq ly;
flag, c := ClassicalIsConjugate (G, x, y);
x^c eq y;


=======================================================

> UnipotentClassLabel;
Intrinsic 'UnipotentClassLabel'

Signatures:

    (G::GrpMat, g::GrpMatElt) -> .

        return unipotent conjugacy class label for unipotent element g of 
        classical G; if two elements of G have different labels, then they 
        are not conjugate; two elements of an isometry group G are conjugate 
        in G if and only if they have same label.

e.g. 

G := GOPlus (8, 9);
repeat x := Random (G); until IsUnipotent (x);
y := x^Random (G);
lx := UnipotentClassLabel (G, x);
ly := UnipotentClassLabel (G, y);
lx eq ly;
flag, c := UnipotentIsConjugate (G, x, y);
x^c eq y;


==================================

> NumberOfClasses;

Intrinsic 'NumberOfClasses'


   (type::MonStgElt, n::RngIntElt) -> RngUPolElt

        The number of conjugacy classes of finite isometry group of the given
        type as a polynomial in q.

* To preserve compatability with existing intrinsic 
* here type is one of: 
linear, GL, unitary, GU, symplecticOdd, SpOdd, symplecticEven, SpEven, orthogonalplusEven, GO+Even, 
orthogonalplusOdd, GO+Odd, orthogonalminusEven, GO-Even, orthogonalminusOdd, GO-Odd, 
orthogonalOdd, GO, conformalUnitary, CU

* n is degree of natural representation

* note this function applies to isometry group only 

e.g. 
f := NumberOfClasses ("orthogonalplusOdd", 8); 
Evaluate (f, 5); // number of classes in GO+(8, 5)

f := NumberOfClasses ("GO-Odd", 8); 
Evaluate (f, 5); // number of classes in GO-(8, 5)
